properties.Name: EquifaxCompanyProfile
properties.Description:
Provides the business name and address on the returned folder which most closely matches your Equifax ePORT® inquiry information, as well as firmographic information about that location. If a legal name is available, it is also returned. Company name, address and firmographics for the registered site are also returned.

The EFX ID™ is a unique and persistent nine-digit number that identifies and tracks the business unit with which you have the credit relationship; if the EFX ID is used on the inquiry, then only the EFX ID is used to locate a folder and the business name and address associated with that EFX ID are returned.

Columns.Name: EfxId
Columns.Description: The EFX ID™ is a unique and persistent nine-digit number that identifies and tracks the business unit with which you have the credit relationship;

Columns.Name: ProfileTimestamp
Columns.Description:
Provides the timestamp when the inquiry was made as recorded
by Equifax (Eastern Time).

Columns.Name: CompanyAddress
Columns.Description: The 'street/po box' component of the company address.

Columns.Name: CompanyCity
Columns.Description: The city component of the company address.

Columns.Name: CompanyState
Columns.Description: The 'state' component of the company address.

Columns.Name: CompanyZipCode
Columns.Description: The 'zip code' component of the company address.

Columns.Name: BusinessType
Columns.Description:
The type of business.

Ex:
- Corporation

Columns.Name: EstablishedDate
Columns.Description: The date the company was established.

Columns.Name: OwnershipType
Columns.Description:
The type of company ownership.

Ex:
- Private

Columns.Name: LocationType
Columns.Description:
The type of company location.

Ex:
- Branch
- Headquarters

Columns.Name: AnnualSalesRangeAmount
Columns.Description:
The company annual sales range.

Ex:
$500,000-$999,999

Columns.Name: UltimateParentName
Columns.Description: The name of the company's ultimate parent legal entity.
